# CombatView.gd
# The battle screen, Final Fantasy style: the four slotted minions cycle
# attacks against a group of foes or a single boss.
#
# The engine is ATB "wait mode": every combatant has a charge gauge that
# fills over time (speed stat scales the rate). When a minion's gauge
# fills, time STOPS and the command menu serves them — unless AUTO is on,
# in which case they attack on their own and time never stops. Enemies
# act the moment their hidden gauges fill.
#
# Commands: Attack (ATK ± 15%), Guard (halve damage until their next
# turn), inked active runes (heavy strike, once per fight each), Flee.
# Bosses telegraph their all-party slam one turn ahead and enrage as
# health quarters break. Victory pays each foe's gold, loot roll, and
# minion XP to the survivors.
extends PanelContainer

# Lanternlight tokens
